WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.300
Here are five data validation libraries for running data quality checks on your Polars data frames.

00:00:05.300 --> 00:00:09.300
1. Pandera. Schema-first validation with statistical tests.

00:00:09.300 --> 00:00:14.200
Pandera has a heavy emphasis on statistical validation, like hypothesis testing.

00:00:14.200 --> 00:00:18.100
2. Petito. Pydantic-style data models for data frames.

00:00:18.100 --> 00:00:23.900
Petito emphasizes integration with existing Pydantic workflows and object modeling.

00:00:23.900 --> 00:00:28.100
3. Pointblank. Pointblank is a comprehensive validation library

00:00:28.100 --> 00:00:34.799
that focuses on step-by-step validation and results in beautiful interactive HTML reports

00:00:34.799 --> 00:00:36.900
perfect for sharing with stakeholders.

00:00:36.900 --> 00:00:41.200
4. Validupci. Composable checks with smart failure handling.

00:00:41.200 --> 00:00:45.900
Validupci prioritizes flexibility and operational robustness.

00:00:45.900 --> 00:00:50.599
5. DataFramely. Type-safe schema validation with advanced features.

00:00:50.599 --> 00:00:55.299
DataFramely emphasizes relational data integrity and type safety.

00:00:55.299 --> 00:01:00.200
If you like this list, check out Rich Ianan's original post, linked in the description,

00:01:00.200 --> 00:01:03.200
and subscribe for more updates from Posit.

